00:01:03.000 --> 00:01:16.000
To be honest, there really isn’t a lot that I’ve done for the team. When I joined the team, I thought a lot about solidifying the basics.

00:01:17.000 --> 00:01:32.000
And basically what that means is that I wanted to make sure the players had an intense practice environment and I also wanted to make sure the players could focus properly.

00:01:33.000 --> 00:02:02.000
Another thing I worked on, was to make sure that the team developed coach-player relationships and player-player relationships. Honestly, I have a lot more things I want to get done with the team but the time was so short that I just haven’t been able to do much.

00:02:27.000 --> 00:02:47.000
First off, the most important thing is that there has to be belief between the coaching staff and the players.The players should trust and see that their coaches are serious about the game and are working hard for them.   

00:02:48.000 --> 00:03:00.000
The players need to acknowledge that the coaching staff is really jumping through hoops just for the players’ sake. However, just believing is not everything.

00:03:16.000 --> 00:03:29.000
Which is why secondly, there has to be distinct synchronization within the team. It can’t just be words. Individually, and together... Err...

00:03:30.000 --> 00:03:35.000
